{
  "texts": [
    "In order to avoid this dependency, an earlier study 41 related B ðnÞ i to A ðnÞ i via an auxiliary parameter α ðnÞ i = def A ðnÞ i > 0 and B ðnÞ i = def α ðnÞ i + P j W ðnÞ ij.",
    "We use this latter model as a comparison point with the choice α ðnÞ i = 1, and call it the α1-model.",
    "It is known that any ReLU network can be mapped to the α1-model 41, but the mapping theory can be extended to our more general model with arbitrary parameters B ðnÞ i.",
    "In the following, we set always A ðnÞ i = 0, but keep B ðnÞ i arbitrary.",
    "We now describe an exact reverse mapping which uniquely defines the parameters of an equivalent ReLU network (up to the intrinsic scaling symmetry of ReLU units) with the same architecture as that of the SNN."
  ]
}